               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Risālah-'i z̤arbat-i Ḥaydarīyah by al-Fāz̤il al-Rashīd</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010112931 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2012000503" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Delhi_Persian_1576x-item1">
                     <textLang mainLang="fa" otherLangs="ar">Persian, Arabic </textLang>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22173">Risālah-'i z̤arbat-i Ḥaydarīyah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_22173">رسالهٴ ضربت حيدريّه</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Severely damaged fragment of a copy of the third volume of a Shīʿī polemical treatise on the virtues of <persName key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657175.0x000001 viaf_34436377" role="subject">Imām ʿAlī</persName> assembled from a variety of primarily Sunnī authorities, entitled <title key="work_22173">Risālah-'i z̤arbat-i Ḥaydarīyah</title>, by an author identified by the epithet <persName key="person_f8068" role="aut">al-Fāz̤il al-Rashīd</persName>, which is probably not the author’s proper name. 
                        </p>
                        <p>Extensive quotations in Arabic cited throughout. 
</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 265v): completed 7 Shavvāl 1253/4 January 1838. 
</p>
                        <p>Extensive annotations in margins in parts. 
</p>
                        <p>Multiple cursive nastaʿlīq-based hands; occasional use of naskh, especially for the colophon. 
</p>
                        <p>Condition extremely fragile at opening and end. Not suitable for handling. </p>
                        <p>Severely weathered, depredated, stained, and cropped, with only fragments of the opening leaves extant. 
</p>
                     </note>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f8068">al-Fāz̤il al-Rashīd</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="person_f8068">الفاضل الرّشيد</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
